---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Ensley Rising | Who Is Abebe?">

  <Header>
    <Fragment slot="title">Ensley Rising</Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      A public-records review of archived Ensley Rising material, Ramsay-McCormack
      reporting, and a separate Abebe Blackbelt Ventures lead.
    </Fragment>
  </Header>

  <main class="article-wrap">
    <article class="article-body report-page">

      <p class="lede">
        Ensley Rising is part of the broader research file because archived
        material and local reporting place Mike Abebe in the same Birmingham
        development context as Carlton Brown and Gizman Abbas.
      </p>

      <div class="notice-box">
        <strong>Scope:</strong>
        This report compares archived web captures, the current Ensley Rising
        website, BirminghamWatch reporting, and entity references. It does not
        claim private knowledge of any internal relationship or later separation.
      </div>

      <h2>Archived Ensley Rising Page</h2>

      <p>
        The archived Ensley Rising website preserved by the Wayback Machine is
        a key source for the older team context.
      </p>

      <a
        class="document-row"
        href="https://web.archive.org/web/20201121181912/https://www.ensleyrising.com/"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <span>Wayback Capture</span>
        <strong>Ensley Rising archived website</strong>
        <p>Archived November 21, 2020 by the Internet Archive Wayback Machine.</p>
      </a>

      <figure class="report-figure">
        <img
          src="/images/entities/ensley-rising-wayback-caputre-may-21-2020.png"
          alt="Ensley Rising Wayback screenshot showing team members"
        />
        <figcaption>
          Archived Ensley Rising team capture showing Mike Abebe, Carlton Brown,
          and Gizman Abbas in principal roles.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <div class="notice-box">
        <strong>Current-site update:</strong>
        The current Abebe Ventures leadership page now uses the same Mike Abebe
        portrait that appears in the older Ensley Rising archive trail. This
        supports the image identification without changing the report's scope:
        Ensley Rising remains an Abebe background lead, not a confirmed
        St. George Crossing connection.
        <a href="https://www.abebe.com/leadership" target="_blank">Open Abebe.com leadership page</a>.
      </div>

      <h2>Current Site Contrast</h2>

      <p>
        The current public Ensley Rising website remains online, but the live
        team material reviewed during this archive pass no longer shows Mike
        Abebe listed. The current site still shows Carlton Brown and Gizman
        Abbas in the team section.
      </p>

      <a class="document-row" href="https://www.ensleyrising.com/" target="_blank">
        <span>Live Website</span>
        <strong>Ensley Rising</strong>
        <p>Current public website reviewed for contrast with archived captures.</p>
      </a>

      <h2>Ramsay-McCormack Reporting</h2>

      <p>
        BirminghamWatch reported in 2019 that the City of Birmingham selected
        Ensley District Developers, LLC for the Ramsay-McCormack Building, naming
        a developer team that included Irvin Henderson, Carlton Brown, Mike Abebe,
        and Gizman Abbas.
      </p>

      <a
        class="document-row"
        href="https://birminghamwatch.org/2019/10/22/city-allocates-4m-emergency-funding-rehab-ramsay-mccormack/"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <span>Local Reporting</span>
        <strong>City Allocates $4M in Emergency Funding to Rehab Ramsay-McCormack</strong>
        <p>BirminghamWatch article published October 22, 2019 by Sam Prickett.</p>
      </a>

      <blockquote class="report-quote">
        "a team of developers that includes Irvin Henderson, Carlton Brown, Mike Abebe and Gizman Abbas"
      </blockquote>

      <h2>Separate Alabama Lead: Abebe Blackbelt Ventures</h2>

      <p>
        The entity research file also includes Abebe Blackbelt Ventures LLC in
        Alabama. At this stage, the archive has not confirmed that Abebe Blackbelt
        Ventures LLC is connected to Ensley Rising or the Ramsay-McCormack project.
        It is included here as a separate Alabama property/entity lead that may
        need additional review.
      </p>

      <a
        class="document-row"
        href="https://properties.madeinmacon.com/files/properties/attachment-1a-business-case-site-advantages-location-and-area-overview-highway-199-site-670e8d8ae542f222341734.pdf"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <span>Property PDF</span>
        <strong>Highway 199 Site - Tuskegee, Alabama</strong>
        <p>
          Macon County site document listing Abebe Blackbelt Ventures LLC as the
          current owner of the Highway 199 and Midway Road site.
        </p>
      </a>

      <table class="report-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>State</th>
            <th>Entity</th>
            <th>Control No.</th>
            <th>Principal Office</th>
            <th>Registered Agent</th>
            <th>Status</th>
            <th>Related Site</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>

        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>AL</td>
            <td>Abebe Blackbelt Ventures LLC</td>
            <td>000-866-410</td>
            <td>2513 31st St SW, Birmingham, AL 35221</td>
            <td>Mekonnen Abebe</td>
            <td>Exists</td>
            <td>Highway 199 and Midway Road, Tuskegee, AL</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Working Notes</h2>

      <div class="fact-grid">
        <div class="fact-card">
          <span>Verified</span>
          <p>
            BirminghamWatch named Mike Abebe, Carlton Brown, and Gizman Abbas
            in the Ensley District Developers team context for Ramsay-McCormack.
            A Macon County site PDF also lists Abebe Blackbelt Ventures LLC as
            the current owner of the Highway 199 and Midway Road site. These are
            separate documented facts unless additional records connect them.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="fact-card">
          <span>Observation</span>
          <p>
            The archived Ensley Rising capture shows Mike Abebe in older team
            material, while the current live site reviewed here does not show
            Mike Abebe in the visible team list. Abebe Blackbelt Ventures appears
            to be a separate Alabama lead unless more source material ties it back
            to Ensley Rising. The updated Abebe.com leadership page now supports
            the portrait attribution used for the older archive trail.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="fact-card">
          <span>Open Question</span>
          <p>
            Additional source records are needed to determine whether Mike Abebe's
            role ended, changed, or was removed from the website for another reason.
            Additional records are also needed before connecting Abebe Blackbelt
            Ventures LLC to Ensley Rising.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <a class="section-card" href="/reports/direct-invest-group">
        <span>Related Thread</span>
        <h3>Direct Invest Group</h3>
        <p>
          Carlton Brown, Mike Abebe, and Gizman Abbas also appear together in
          archived Direct Invest partner material.
        </p>
      </a>

    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />

</BaseLayout>
